Introduction
- Main point: Characterization of $e_it$ across $i=1, \ldots, 168$ countries and for $t=1950, 2014$ years.
- Explicitly Marxian, though not dogmatic, framework.
- Organization of the book.

Framework
- Dialectical materialism: Humans are a part of nature with specific properties.
- Historical materialism: Production = history.  Labor.
- Political economy: Value, surplus value.
- Critique of economics: Value as measure of relative social importance.

Empirical material: PWT 9.0
- Description
- National accounting categories and their mapping to Marxian categories

Empirical methods: Econometrics
- Time series VAR
- Cross sectional
- Panel

